1. Introduction
The Fitness Goal Tracking Dashboard is a web-based application designed to help individuals systematically monitor, manage, and achieve their fitness goals. In today’s fast-paced lifestyle, many people struggle to maintain consistency in their workouts and track their physical progress effectively. This project addresses that gap by providing a centralized platform where users can log their daily workouts and visualize their progress through structured reports and dashboards.
The system enables users to record key fitness activities such as exercises performed, sets, repetitions, duration, and calories burned. It further transforms this raw data into meaningful insights using charts and progress reports, helping users stay motivated and make informed decisions about their fitness routines.
This project follows the principles of Software Project Management, covering all phases from initiation and planning to execution, monitoring, and closure. It not only focuses on building a functional system but also emphasizes proper project governance, risk management, quality assurance, and stakeholder communication.
Overall, the Fitness Goal Tracking Dashboard aims to promote a disciplined and data-driven approach to fitness while demonstrating the practical application of project management concepts in software development.















2. Project Charter 
The project titled “Fitness Goal Tracking Dashboard: Workout Logging + Progress Reports” focuses on developing a web-based system that helps users effectively track their fitness activities and monitor progress. Many individuals face difficulty in maintaining consistency in workouts due to the lack of proper tracking tools and meaningful insights. Traditional methods fail to provide visualization and structured reports, which reduces motivation. This project aims to solve this problem by offering a centralized dashboard for logging workouts and analyzing progress.
Project Objectives
•	To design a user-friendly fitness tracking dashboard 
•	To enable users to log daily workout activities 
•	To generate weekly and monthly progress reports 
•	To help users set and achieve fitness goals 
•	To apply Software Project Management concepts in real implementation

High-Level Requirements
•	User registration and login system 
•	Workout logging module (exercise, reps, sets, duration) 
•	Dashboard with charts and analytics 
•	Goal-setting feature 
•	Progress report generation (weekly/monthly) 

