3. Feasibility Study (TELOS Framework)
The feasibility study evaluates whether the Fitness Goal Tracking Dashboard project is practical and achievable within the given constraints using the TELOS framework.

1. Technical Feasibility
The project is technically feasible as it can be developed using basic web technologies such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. A simple database (like MySQL or local storage) can be used to store user data and workout logs. The required tools and technologies are easily available and familiar at an academic level. No advanced infrastructure or complex integrations are needed, making the system easy to design, develop, and deploy.

2. Economic Feasibility
The project is economically viable as it requires minimal investment. Since it is a student project, most tools (such as code editors, browsers, and hosting platforms) are free or open-source. There are no significant hardware or software costs involved. Hence, the overall development cost remains very low and affordable.

 3. Legal Feasibility
The project does not involve any legal complications as it does not handle sensitive personal or financial data. It is intended for academic purposes and follows standard ethical practices. Proper care will be taken to ensure that user data is handled responsibly and no copyrighted material is misused.

 4. Operational Feasibility
The system is easy to operate and user-friendly. Users can easily log their workouts and view progress without requiring technical expertise. The interface will be simple and intuitive, ensuring smooth interaction. The system fulfills the intended purpose of helping users track fitness goals effectively.

5. Schedule Feasibility
The project can be completed within the given semester timeline. It will be developed in phases such as planning, design, development, testing, and deployment. Since the scope is limited and well-defined, the project is achievable within the allocated time frame.



4. Scope Statement
The Fitness Goal Tracking Dashboard: Workout Logging + Progress Reports project focuses on developing a web-based application that enables users to efficiently track their fitness activities and monitor their progress over time. The system will allow users to log workout details such as exercises, sets, repetitions, and duration, and present this data through a structured dashboard with visual reports. The primary goal is to provide a simple, user-friendly platform that helps individuals stay consistent with their fitness routines and achieve their goals through better tracking and analysis.
The scope of this project includes core functionalities such as user authentication, workout logging, progress visualization through charts, goal setting, and generation of weekly or monthly reports. The system will be designed using basic web technologies and will focus on usability and clarity rather than complex features.
However, the project excludes advanced functionalities such as integration with wearable fitness devices, AI-based recommendations, live coaching features, and mobile application development. By clearly defining these boundaries, the project ensures focused development, avoids scope creep, and remains achievable within the given time and resource constraints.
In-Scope Features
The following functionalities are included in the project:
•	User registration and login system 
•	Workout logging (exercise name, sets, repetitions, duration) 
•	Dashboard for visualizing progress (charts, summaries) 
•	Goal setting (e.g., weight loss, muscle gain) 
•	Weekly and monthly progress reports 
•	Basic, user-friendly web interface (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) 

Out-of-Scope Exclusions
The following functionalities are not included in the project:
•	Integration with wearable devices (fitness bands, smartwatches) 
•	AI-based workout or diet recommendations 
•	Live coaching or trainer interaction features 
•	Mobile application development (only web-based system) 
•	Advanced analytics or real-time performance tracking 


5. SMART Project Objectives
The objectives of the Fitness Goal Tracking Dashboard are defined using the SMART criteria (Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, Time-bound) to ensure clarity and successful project completion.
•	Specific:
Develop a web-based dashboard that allows users to log workouts, set fitness goals, and track progress through visual reports. 
•	Measurable: 
o	Enable logging of at least 10 types of exercises 
o	Generate weekly and monthly progress reports 
o	Ensure the system can handle multiple user entries without errors 
•	Achievable:
The project will be developed using basic technologies like HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, making it feasible within the available skills and resources of a student. 
•	Relevant:
The project addresses a real-world problem of fitness tracking and aligns with academic requirements of Software Project Management, ensuring practical application of concepts. 
•	Time-bound:
The project will be completed within 8 weeks, covering all phases including planning, design, development, testing, and final submission. 









